INUMBER 818
NAME 994
MISC
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
VARIABLE owstick
IFPREVERB TURN -1
  CLEARVERB
   ADD owstick 1
    IFVAR owstick = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You twist the top end of the stick causing that portion to slide out, lengthening the stick.
      ECHO OTHERS %N twists the top end of the stick causing that portion to slide out, lengthening the entire stick.
    ENDIF
     IFVAR owstick = 2
       ECHO PLAYER You twist the elongated portion, causing the top portion to slide into the lower portion.
       ECHO OTHERS %N twists the elongated portion, causing the top portion of the rune stick to slide into the lower portion.
       EQUAL owstick 0
     ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK -1
  CLEARVERB
   IFVAR owstick = 0
     ECHO PLAYER Shimmering runes dance along the shortened stick, their meaning lost to you, their meaning lost to you for they look strangely alien. A closer examination reveals that many of the runes contain inworked images of nature. A few of the runes seem to be only half there, specifically, the ones towards the center of the stick.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR owstick = 1
     ECHO PLAYER Now the stick is elongated, you can make out the deep beauty and power that had been hidden before. They combine with the other runes in a grand display of homage to nature's power.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB CONCENTRATE -1
  IFVAR owstick = 1
   IFVAR RNUM = 2571
     ECHO PLAYER You feel your mind being drawn into the image on the wall...
     ECHO PLAYER You find yourself standing in a beautiful garden, surrounded by twelve robed figures, their faces indistinguishable...
     ECHO PLAYER Each nods slightly to you and then they begin to speak, in turn...
     ECHO PLAYER The first figure says, "Greetings unto you, the finder of the key. The Twelve acknowledge you and the severity of the task that you embark upon."
     ECHO PLAYER The second figure says, "Our lore will aid in healing this world, brought to ruin by the evil of the machines."
     ECHO PLAYER The third figure says, "Your feet are now upon the path to reach the first lore, the Khonovar."
     ECHO PLAYER The fourth figure says, "From where you found the key, go to the north, into the high peaked stones."
     ECHO PLAYER The fifth figure says, "The palm of Majeries to be found, its power working to open the door,  two full passings of sun and moon, power from each used to open, must be waited."
     ECHO PLAYER The sixth figure says, "Within the ring must the twelve children of the mother dance, to open the portal fair."
     ECHO PLAYER The seventh figure says, "The halls of fire to be passed, oftentimes consumed to be safely passed."
     ECHO PLAYER The eighth figure says, "Guardians, careful for their touch will kill, guard the way. Choose correctly, or your quest will fail."
     ECHO PLAYER The ninth figure says, "The winds of Blood to be ridden, remember that not all things are as they seem.
     ECHO PLAYER The tenth figure says, "Ware ye the doors of the inner chamber, one leads to hope, the others to death and despair."
     ECHO PLAYER The eleventh figure says, "Stand you before the chest of the first, speak the words of nature's grace and take the treasure within."
     ECHO PLAYER The twelfth figure says, "As this is your key to the first, so will the first be the key to the second."
     ECHO PLAYER You feel your mind drawing away from the garden...
     ECHO OTHERS %N stares, transfixedly, at the wall.
   ENDIF
  IFVAR RNUM ! 2571
    ECHO ALL You see the runes dance wildly, pulling from the rune stick, trying to go somehwere, but failing miserably and flowing back onto the stick.
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
 IFVAR owstick ! 1
  ECHO PLAYER The stick seems to throb with a faint hint of blue power, but goes quickly quiescent.
  ECHO OTHERS The rune stick seems to throb with a faint hint of blue power, but quickly goes quiescent.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
