INUMBER 1586
NAME 1140
MISC
WEIGHT 3
VOLUME 3
VARIABLE monwarsprite
VARIABLE monwarsprite1
VARIABLE monwarsprite2
VARIABLE monwarsprite3
VARIABLE monwarsprite4
VARIABLE monwarsprite5
VARIABLE monwarsprite6
VARIABLE monwarsprite7
VARIABLE monwarsprite8
IFPREVERB LOOK -1
  CLEARVERB
   IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
     ECHO PLAYER **Be aware that this is a unique item!**
   ENDIF
     ECHO PLAYER Of a seamless, perfect construction this artifact from a bygone era fairly humms with musical power waiting to be unleashed. Made of polished steel, with strings of a glistening silvery hue, the instrument gleams brightly in any light. Carefully engraved bolts of lightning explode from the bottom, racing up along the neck. A small knob has been unobtrusively placed at the bottom and a long cord with a plug at the end also extends from it.
     ECHO OTHERS %N gazes lovingly at the musical artifact.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH -1
  CLEARVERB
   IFVAR RAC = 7
    IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You are already plugged in.
      ECHO OTHERS %N adjusts the plug, you hear a staticky noise emit from %i.
    ENDIF
     IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 0
       ECHO PLAYER You take the plug, pull open a panel on your right thigh, exposing a small socket and place the plug in the socket. You immediately feel a surge of power flow from you into the guitar. The bolts of lightning on the guitar gleam brightly as the power flows through them.
       ECHO OTHERS %N takes the plug dangling from the guitar, pulls open a panel on %h right thigh, exposing a small socket, and then places the plug into the socket. A loud humming noise fills the air, interspersed with crackling, emitting from %N. The lightning bolts on the guitar glow brightly as power surges through them.
       EQUAL ITEMBIT0 1
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
     IFVAR RAC ! 7
       ECHO PLAYER You stare confusedly at the plug.
       ECHO OTHERS %N stares confusedly at the plug.
     ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PULL -1
  CLEARVERB
   IFVAR RAC = 7
    IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER The guitar isnt even plugged in, so it's impossible to take it out.
    ENDIF
     IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 1
       ECHO PLAYER You pull the plug from the socket and bow with a flourish.
       ECHO OTHERS %N pulls the plug from the socket and bows with a flouris.
       EQUAL ITEMBIT0 0
       EQUAL monwarsprite 0
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
     IFVAR RAC ! 7
       ECHO PLAYER Fiddling around with the plug doesn't get you anywhere.
       ECHO OTHERS %N fiddles around with the cord and the plug, getting nowhere in the process.
     ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TURN -1
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 1
   ADD monwarsprite 1
    IFVAR monwarsprite = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You turn the dial to the first setting. The guitar makes a loud humming noise.
      ECHO OTHERS %N turns the dial to the first setting. The guitar makes a loud humming noise.
    ENDIF
     IFVAR monwarsprite = 2
       ECHO PLAYER You turn the dial to the second, and loudest, setting. The guitar makes a nearly deafening humming noise.
       ECHO OTHERS %N turns the dial to the second setting. The guitar makes a nearly deafening humming noise.
     ENDIF
      IFVAR monwarsprite = 3
        ECHO PLAYER You turn the dial to zero.
        ECHO OTHERS %N turns the dial to zero.
        EQUAL monwarsprite 0
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 0
     ECHO PLAYER You can't do that, the guitar isn't plugged in.
     ECHO OTHERS %N fiddles with the dial but nothing happens.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PLAY -1
  CLEARVERB
  EQUAL monwarsprite1 EXITN
  EQUAL monwarsprite2 EXITNE
  EQUAL monwarsprite3 EXITE
  EQUAL monwarsprite4 EXITSE
  EQUAL monwarsprite5 EXITS
  EQUAL monwarsprite6 EXITSW
  EQUAL monwarsprite7 EXITW
  EQUAL monwarsprite8 EXITNW
  IFVAR monwarsprite = 0
    ECHO PLAYER You plink the strings but all that emerges is a tinny sound as the volume has not been turned on.
    ECHO OTHERS %N plinks the strings but all that emerges is a tinny, metallic sound.
  ENDIF
   IFVAR monwarsprite = 1
     ECHO ALL %N's fingers dance easily across the strings of the guitar coaxing forth a wondrous melody that reaches into the air and into your soul, drawing forth images of beauty and deeply felt joy.
   ENDIF
    IFVAR monwarsprite = 2
      ECHO ALL Like the roar of thunder, music explodes from the guitar that %N plays. %H fingers are blurs across the strings, ranging up and down to draw forth the raw power of music from the wondrous instrument. Music as loud as anything you've ever heard, but with a deep beauty that is impossible to ignore as it tugs at your heart!
     IFVAR EXITN ! -1
      AFFECT EXITN
      ECHO ALL Like a wave of thunder music reaches you from the south its power enough to stagger and overwhelm you with its raw power and beauty. Glancing that way you see %N playing %h guitar like a person possesed.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR EXITNE ! -1
      AFFECT EXITNE
      ECHO ALL Like a wave of thunder music reaches you from the southwest its power enough to stagger and overwhelm you with its raw power and beauty. Glancing that way you see %N playing %h guitar like a person possesed.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR EXITE ! -1
      AFFECT EXITE
      ECHO ALL Like a wave of thunder music reaches you from the west its power enough to stagger and overwhelm you with its raw power and beauty. Glancing that way you see %N playing %h guitar like a person possesed.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR EXITSE ! -1
      AFFECT EXITSE
      ECHO ALL Like a wave of thunder music reaches you from the northwest its power enough to stagger and overwhelm you with its raw power and beauty. Glancing that way you see %N playing %h guitar like a person possesed.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR EXITS ! -1
      AFFECT EXITS
      ECHO ALL Like a wave of thunder music reaches you from the north its power enough to stagger and overwhelm you with its raw power and beauty. Glancing that way you see %N playing %h guitar like a person possesed.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR EXITSW ! -1
      AFFECT EXITSW
      ECHO ALL Like a wave of thunder music reaches you from the northeast its power enough to stagger and overwhelm you with its raw power and beauty. Glancing that way you see %N playing %h guitar like a person possesed.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR EXITW ! -1
      AFFECT EXITW
      ECHO ALL Like a wave of thunder music reaches you from the east its power enough to stagger and overwhelm you with its raw power and beauty. Glancing that way you see %N playing %h guitar like a person possesed.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR EXITNW ! -1
